RACE.FOOTNOTES: GENTLEMAN'S SECRET rated off of the early pace while not far back, steadied slightly while in tight quarters heading to the turn, advanced while three wide nearing the quarter marker, confronted OBVIOUS approaching the furlong pole, disposed of the runner-up leaving the furlong marker and kept to task in the final stages to prove best. OBVIOUS bobbled at the start and was off a step slowly, rushed up heading to the turn and pressed the pace into the bend, took a narrow lead nearing the quarter marker, was confronted by GENTLEMAN'S SECRET nearing mid-stretch, could not hold keep pace with the winner in deep stretch and held safely in the end for second. EMERALD MAGIC took back off of the moderate early pace, saved ground to the quarter marker, was roused three wide into the stretch, closed in the late stages and was up in the final strides to secure third. MINOSO stalked the moderate early pace from the inside, made a bit of headway nearing mid-stretch, could not sustain that run in the final furlong and was outfinished for third. RHODIUM RUNNER broke alertly and contested the early pace, battled for pace duties with OBVIOUS to the quarter marker, was overtaken in upper stretch, chased while still in aim to mid-stretch and faded in the final stages.

Non-winners Of Two Races Since February 1 Allowed 3 lbs. A Race Since Then Allowed 5 lbs. Claiming Price $8,0 00 (Maiden, Claiming And Starter Races For $3,500 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: OUR EXPECTATION was allowed to settle off of the decent early pace, raced two wide into the turn, was roused four wide into the stretch, ran evenly to the furlong marker, closed well in deep stretch, caught STANFORD BAY at the the sixteenth-marker and kept to task in the final stages to prevail over the oncoming runner-up. HUNTERS GHOST chased the decent early pace while outside of rivals, raced four wide into the turn, angled to the three path nearing the quarter marker, advanced nearing the furlong grounds, was outkicked by the winner in the late stages, finished well in deep stretch and was second best. STANFORD BAY broke alertly and showed good early speed, dictated terms to the turn, drew to a clear lead approaching the top of the lane, remained clear to mid-stretch, was overtaken at the sixteenth-marker and just held for the show. SATANTA was unhurried in the early stages, saved ground to the quarter marker, swung two wide for the drive, offered a late rally inside of the furlong marker and just missed for the show. AMANOFMYSTATURE stalked the early fractions, raced three wide into the turn then angled to the two path while between runners, lost ground approaching the top of the lane, ran evenly to mid-stretch, took up while in tight quarters just inside of the furlong pole and lacked a late response. REFI NOW tracked the decent early pace, raced two wide into the turn then slipped to the inside nearing the quarter marker, chased the pacesetter to mid-stretch, drifted out just inside of the furlong marker, made contact with AMANOFMYSTATURE and gave way in the late stages. THERE WAS A STEWARDS' INQUIRY INTO THE INCIDENT INSIDE OF THE FURLONG MARKER INVOLVING AMANOFMYSTATURE AND REFI NOW. IN A UNANIMOUS DECISION, THE STEWARDS RULED THAT REFI NOW DRIFTED OUT AND INTERFERED WITH AMANOFMYSTATURE BUT DUE TO AMANOFMYSTATURE FINISHING AHEAD OF REFI NOW, THERE WOULD BE NO CHANGE TO THE ORDER OF FINISH. THE RIDER OF AMANOFMYSTATURE ALSO CLAIMED FOUL AGAINST THE RIDER OF REFI NOW.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: POUR ON THE COLE tracked the leaders along the first turn, settled off of the contentious pace along the backstretch run, loomed four wide nearing the quarter marker, came five wide into the stretch, made a grinding rally in the drive, caught ON RAGLAN ROAD in deep stretch, took command at the sixteenth-marker and kept to task in the final strides to prevail. ON RAGLAN ROAD tracked the decent early fractions, maintained position through the backstretch run, mounted a two wide bid approaching the quarter marker, confronted TIZONA and battled with that rival to mid-stretch, took a narrow lead into the final furlong, could not hold off the oncoming winner in deep stretch and just held for the place on the wire. DI LAURIAN broke alertly, set the early pace then ceded the lead along the backstretch run to TIZONA, rated off of that rival's pace heading to the second turn, advanced while saving ground nearing the quarter marker, swung three wide for the drive, lost ground heading to mid-stretch, re-rallied late but was outkicked in deep stretch and just missed for the place, while clear of the rest for the show. TIZONA was forwardly placed into the first turn, stalked the pace into the backstretch run then took command heading to the half-mile marker, drew to a clear lead approaching the far turn, came under pressure nearing the quarter marker, battled with ON RAGLAN ROAD to mid-stretch and faded in the final furlong. RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 9 5 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 72. Maiden Claiming Purse 17000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000, if for $22,500, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: HOT CHICKS ONLY broke in at the start, made light contact with NEVER HAD I EVER then quickly joined the leading group racing four wide, backed off a bit before the turn, then displayed a good turn of foot on the turn becoming the outside horse in a trio contesting the lead at the top of the stretch, finished best under a strong hand ride and had enough to hold off a fast closing DUPLICATION at the wire. DUPLICATION broke well and was part of the early pace, dropped off the pace heading into the turn, re-rallied and shifted to the outside approaching the quarter pole, tipped out four wide for the stretch run and closed stoutly to just miss. HOWDOYALIKEMENOW broke alertly and hustled to gain the early lead, held the lead through the turn, responded when challenged by a pair near the quarter pole, battled gamely to the wire but was outfinished in the end. MOTOWN CLASSIC was away well then outrun in the early stages, gradually worked over to the rail before the turn, got a clear run through the turn and into the stretch, finished up well. NEVER HAD I EVER good off to a good start and was part of the early pace picture, chased HOWDOYALIKEMENOW to the turn then moved in tandem with HOT CHICKS ONLY to pressure the early pacesetter, was between horse for the battle turning for home but weakened mid-stretch. CANTILEVER outrun early, was part of the trailing pack and racing four wide through the early stages, was put into a drive with three furlongs to run while still wide around the turn and finished somewhat one-paced and a little green to the wire, unable to improve position. COOPERKLIMT was hustled from the gate but unable to engage in the early pace, was green and climbed nearing the turn, jumped shadows at the seven-sixteenths marker, lost momentum and fell several lengths behind the field, was kept to task and finished with some interest. SMOKIN BLAZE mid-pack early, had trouble keeping up passing the five-sixteenths pole and had nothing to offer in the stretch. THERE WAS A STEWARDS' INQUIRY INVOLVING THE RUN INTO THE TURN. THE STEWARDS RULED IN A UNANIMOUS DECISION THAT COOPERKLIMT WAS GREEN, JUMPED SHADOWS AND WAS TAKEN UP BY HIS RIDER NEARING THE THREE-FURLONG MARKER AND THAT THERE WOULD BE NO ACTION TAKEN STEMMING FROM THAT INCIDENT.
